.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,1520,1963]" pageId="4" pageNumber="63">
This fish is very rare and only a few specimens are deposited in collections around the world besides the Brazilian pair. The meristic and morphometric data for these specimens and that of selected literature are in 
<tableCitation box="[151,315,1747,1773]" captionStart-0="TABLE 2 - A" captionStart-1="TABLE 2 - B" captionStartId-0="5.[151,239,151,175]" captionStartId-1="5.[151,241,583,607]" captionTargetBox-0="[151,1422,277,513]" captionTargetBox-1="[151,1436,666,1105]" captionTargetPageId-0="5" captionTargetPageId-1="5" captionText-0="TABLE 2 - A. Verilus sordidus. Meristic data of selected papers." captionText-1="TABLE 2 - B. Verilus sordidus. Selected proportional measurements in thousands of SL. Number of specimens as in Table 2 - A." httpUri-0="http://table.plazi.org/id/0EB0667D9D4BFFF3FF0B5FB6035AFF10" httpUri-1="http://table.plazi.org/id/0EB0667D9D4BFFF3FF0B5D66016CFDC0" pageId="4" pageNumber="63" tableUuid-0="0EB0667D9D4BFFF3FF0B5FB6035AFF10" tableUuid-1="0EB0667D9D4BFFF3FF0B5D66016CFDC0">
Tables 
<number box="[234,249,1747,1773]" pageId="4" pageNumber="63" value="2.0">2</number>
.A–B
</tableCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,1520,1963]" pageId="4" pageNumber="63">
The specimens from Bahia are the 
<number box="[616,645,1787,1813]" pageId="4" pageNumber="63" value="12.0">12</number>
th and 
<number box="[718,747,1787,1813]" pageId="4" pageNumber="63" value="13.0">13</number>
th ever deposited in scientific institutions, (not considering 
<collectionCode LSID="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34871" box="[151,236,1825,1851]" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34871" name="Smithsonian Institution, National Museum of Natural History" pageId="4" pageNumber="63">USNM</collectionCode>
<number box="[243,331,1825,1851]" pageId="4" pageNumber="63" value="271959.0">271959</number>
(
<number box="[350,363,1825,1851]" pageId="4" pageNumber="63" value="1.0">1</number>
, skull, dry osteological preparation, SL unknown, off 
<collectingCountry box="[998,1063,1825,1851]" name="Cuba" pageId="4" pageNumber="63">Cuba</collectingCountry>
, coll. by F. Poey, apparently the same specimen of 
<collectionCode LSID="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34871" box="[373,458,1862,1888]" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34871" name="Smithsonian Institution, National Museum of Natural History" pageId="4" pageNumber="63">USNM</collectionCode>
<number box="[467,561,1862,1888]" pageId="4" pageNumber="63" value="271973.0">271973</number>
), and present the first record of the species for the Southwestern Atlantic Ocean and 
<collectingCountry box="[286,362,1899,1925]" name="Brazil" pageId="4" pageNumber="63">Brazil</collectingCountry>
. The species range is extended by about 
<quantity box="[851,964,1899,1925]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.8" pageId="4" pageNumber="63" unit="km" value="3.8">3,800 km</quantity>
southwards in a straight line and 
<quantity metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.6" pageId="4" pageNumber="63" unit="km" value="4.6">4,600 km</quantity>
along the South American coastline.
</paragraph>
